      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay okay calm down lol i'm not saying i'll stop it today. i'm just frustrated. but if vitamin k is what makes the warfarin stop working, wouldn't that mean if i just took enough of it i could basically control my level myself? like if i know how much k is in a spinach smoothie, can't i just use that to keep my levels steady so i don't need the doctor to do the blood tests every week?",
