      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, you cannot reliably control your INR or safely stop warfarin by just eating specific amounts of vitamin K because your body's absorption and metabolism vary wildly from day to day. Even small, uncontrolled fluctuations in your vitamin K intake are what cause dangerous swings in your blood's clotting ability, leading to either fatal clots or massive bleeds. The only safe way to manage your levels without constant testing is to switch to a different type of blood thinner prescribed by your doctor, as their modern alternatives do not rely on balancing vitamin K.",
